    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-05-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-05-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1460.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence relative to
                    the course of the American minister at La Paz in protecting the interests of
                    British subjects in Bolivia, and particularly with regard to your note of the
                    17th ultimo on the subject, I have the honor to inform you that the Department
                    has received a dispatch from Mr. Bridgman, our minister at La Paz, reporting
                    that at present there is no need of protection for British subjects in Bolivia
                    as everything is quiet there.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
